 Toyota Motor Corp., through its
finance arm, sold $1.29 billion of bonds backed by auto loans,
according to a person familiar with the transaction.  The largest top-rated portion being offered, a $347.1
million slice maturing in 1.9 years, yields 18 basis points more
than the benchmark interest rate, said the person, who declined
